 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucicelygoldenfair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lanys Cheerleader</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/28/02 11:57:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=215.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: elo</span><hr size=1> a stupid reason?<br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
the design of a keyed level to a dungeon is for the individual to possess a key to be able to access that part of the dungeon.  if you are able to circumvent the intended meaning and design of the level through the use of spells, then you are defying what the entire purpose of a keyed level is in the first place.<br>
<br>
what boggles me is why can't players just accept the game for what it is sometimes.  yes, if it is a glaring flaw then speak out and be concerned.  but it is quite obvious that the designer of the shissar temple expected players to take the time to acquire keys for each person that wanted to go to the third floor.  circumventing that is going against game design, and thus a change is going to be made.  so put forth the time and effort to get keys for all people to make it to the third floor, then run amok.  don't circumvent and override game design and intent just cause you are too lazy to farm keys for everyone (you not referring to anyone in particular, used in a general sense).<br>
<br>
what verant should do is make it so that the third floor checks your inventory for a key.  if you don't have it, and try to get to the third floor, it summons you out of the zone and into the grey.  instead, they took the cheap route and screwed over all of us other mages in other guilds who never wanted to circumvent or go above the game design and intent of the floors... who instead merely just wanted to call of hero late adds to our guild raids...<br>
