<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10393">Magelo Profile</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uruanolikm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruanolik M</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/28/02 2:46:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=215.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: elo</span><hr size=1> I think that Verant uses more of a sweeping approach to fixing things 9 out of 10 times.  The whole original CoH nerf was due to an abuse during the Sleeper incident, and they picked an easy target that solved the problem.   Mages have CoH.  CoH was a tactic.  Kill tactic by changing CoH.  <br>
<br>
This is just another shining example of Verant's ability (or lack thereof) to change the game to fit their vision.  Unfortunately at the expense of the player base.  The reason it stings more, is that the mage seems to be an easy target most of the time.  <br>
<br>
