</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugamrok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/28/02 9:21:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=215.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: elo</span><hr size=1> Cicely, it's a stupid reason because not a single keyed area that I've seen in Luclin is requires everyone to have a key.  If you have one key you can keep the door open for everyone, the only thing the nerf prevents is wall exploits.  So, rather than fix the exploit they just make it meaningless to use (not sure if that made sense to anyone else).<br>
